Offline Installation Procedure for Python Packages - CSC CAPTCHA - PROD Environment

Purpose
This document outlines the offline installation steps for the required Python packages needed to configure CSC CAPTCHA functionality in the PROD Environment, where internet access is restricted.
1. Prerequisites
- Python 3.12.3 (64-bit) installed
- .NET Core SDK installed
- Access to an online machine (for initial package downloads)
- Access to transfer files to the offline production machine
2. Required Python Packages
- opencv-python
- paddleocr
- paddlepaddle
- (and their dependencies)
3. Process Overview
Step
Description
1
Download all required packages and dependencies on an online machine
2
Transfer downloaded packages to the offline production machine
3
Install packages locally without internet access
4. Detailed Steps
4.1 On an Online Machine (Preparation)
1. Open Command Prompt or PowerShell.
2. Create a folder to store the packages:
mkdir captcha_packages
cd captcha_packages

3. Download all required packages and their dependencies:
pip download opencv-python -d captcha_packages
pip download paddleocr -d captcha_packages
pip download paddlepaddle -d captcha_packages

4. Verify that all files are downloaded successfully.
4.2 Transfer Files to Offline Machine
- Copy the entire captcha_packages folder to the offline PROD server.
- Suggested directory: C:\captcha_packages
4.3 On the Offline Machine (Installation)
1. Open Command Prompt.
2. Navigate to your Python virtual environment if created:
cd path\to\your\captcha_env\Scripts
activate

3. Install the packages offline using:
pip install --no-index --find-links=C:\captcha_packages opencv-python paddleocr paddlepaddle

4. Confirm successful installation using:
pip list

5. Optional: Installation Automation
You can create a batch file (.bat) for easy installation:
@echo off
cd C:\captcha_packages
call path\to\your\captcha_env\Scripts\activate
pip install --no-index --find-links=C:\captcha_packages opencv-python paddleocr paddlepaddle
echo Installation Completed Successfully!
pause

6. Additional Note: PaddleOCR Model Files
- PaddleOCR may attempt to download pretrained models during its first run.
- To ensure complete offline functionality, it is recommended to pre-download the model files separately and configure PaddleOCR to use local paths.
- Further guidance for offline PaddleOCR model setup can be provided if required.
